git-jira
========

Simple, yet useful git command to set current JIRA ticket you are working on.

Saves time - set once, and it will auto-append JIRA ticket code to your commit
messages.


Installation
------------

Symlink/copy the "bin" directory anywhere so it is visible in your $PATH.

For bash/zsh, you can edit your shell config file like this:

    export PATH=$PATH:/path/to/git-jira/bin/


Usage
-----

git jira [-arg1, --arg2...]
    commit with current JIRA ticket code. Args are passed to 'git commit'.

git jira set [CODE]
    set current JIRA ticket to 'CODE', if specified, or clean existing one.

git jira clean
    clean existing JIRA ticket code.

git jira show
    show current JIRA ticket code.

git jira file
    show the file path where the ticket code is stored.

git jira help
    show help&usage message and exit.
